New Records: Scottie Barnes scored 33 points and had 13 rebounds and 5 assists.
Immanuel Quickley returned from a 22-game absence and scored 21 points with 15 assists and 4 rebounds.
Gradey Dick contributed 22 points, 4 three-pointers, and 3 steals.
Key Match Events: Ja’Kobe Walter’s three-pointer gave Toronto a 45-44 lead with 6:45 left in the second quarter.
Brooklyn responded with an 8-2 burst to take a 65-64 halftime lead.
Noah Clowney left the game with a back injury after falling while rebounding.
Brooklyn’s Maxwell Lewis was helped off the court late in the fourth quarter.
Pre-Game Insights: Immanuel Quickley’s return was a key factor for the Raptors.
RJ Barrett, Bruce Brown, and Cam Thomas were absent due to illness or injury.
Post-Match Reflections: The victory was significant for the Raptors in ending their 11-game skid.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Brooklyn had lost three consecutive games and five of their last six.
The Nets led 33-26 after the first quarter.
